node.text: I have been donating to animals in need for many many years, as you may know my heart is mush for animals and I would do anything for them. It’s hard to know where to donate, where to find an animal to foster and how right!?? There are SO MANY who need help it’s so frustrating! I’ve always wanted to do more even if it’s from afar. Well, my amazing best friend @tamietran sent me an email today and it read... “Congratulations you have been gifted an adoption of Kinyei” I just started bawling lol I’m so touched!! My heart feels so full. Sweet Kinyei’s story is like so many other orphan Elephants. Her mother was found dead and she was wandering all alone near a pack of Lions. No baby should feel that, she was only a few days old.. hungry and scared. I am so thankful to her rescue team Marc Goss of the Mara Elephant Project along with a KWS veterinary officer Dr. Njoroge, Ol Kinyei Conservancy Rangers, Porini Cheetah Camp staff, Mara Elephant Project and the Kenya Wildlife Service. Thank you  @sheldricktrust for giving these orphans a second chance at life and for giving people like me the opportunity to help! I’m SO HAPPY and totally feel like she is mine! I will for sure be going to visit her when travel is safe. If you have been thinking about ways you can give back to animals in great need they have so many others who need foster parents! Please visit @sheldricktrust for photos and stories of other orphans that you can help! 🐘

node.title: My Foster Baby Kinyei 🐘 Please read more tap down 👉🏼

node.text:
Three years ago today I married the man of my dreams. I used to only dream of a love like this, I never thought it could actually exist. Thank you for showing me how real love is supposed to feel, how to trust, and what true happiness means. We were just two strangers who grew up thousands of miles apart...two strangers whose whole life would be a journey towards each other.. We took many different life paths but still, somehow we ended up in the same place at the same time. The universe just has this invisible way of showing you it's listening.  I love you forever @larryenglish_ 🤍
Thank you @lifeasiz for capturing these beautiful memories for us.
Song 🎶 @alaynamusic__

node.text:
Today I wanted to show my appreciation to those who are fighting for all of us everyday. Thank you for standing strong and working overtime. I know it’s just a free lunch, but I hope it helps you know that you are important and mean so much to your community. 
We donated meals to Ronald Reagan @uclahealth @accessanimalhospitals and @vetcancergroup who have been there for my family through some difficult times. I love and appreciate you! 
Thank you so much to @beyondmeat for donating one million meals this month and thank you to @DoorDash for helping me with the deliveries. 🙏🏼 (Don’t worry I triple washed my hands before and after, supplies are scarce but I’m taking precautions)

node.text:
I finally caved and let Larry convince me to workout outside. I usually only like using gym equipment and weights because I hate cardio and anything to do with jumping! As you can see I tried to make the most of it 😜
Just to get moving really helped me feel better and to get some fresh air was just what I needed. I woke up the next morning completely sore so it’s safe to say my body got a great workout. #StayHomeStayFit  @aloyoga 
Song: @saintjhn -Roses

node.text:
This was a special day that I will never forget! Thank you #MSCOceanCay for showing me such beauty and helping me understand more about what’s happening in our oceans. Promoting animal welfare and sustainability is very important to me and I’m so happy to shoot my first @oceandrivemag cover in a place that supports such a great cause!! 🐠🐡🐙🐢🦀
Video: @antonkirindongo @johnhallerfilms

My number is 323 289 6461 📱

node.text:
Have you ever heard the saying “Leaves of three, let it be”? ☘️ Glad someone told me or I would have found out the hard way!

This day reminded me of my childhood back home in Newfoundland! I spent most of my days as a kid in the forest climbing these huge rocks in the woods next to my house. I’d be out there allllll day lol just chillin until I heard my mom screaming my name for dinner. I’d come home smelling like turpentine 😬 Dang I miss those days I can still smell it! 🌲🌲🌲
